                <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ublio</ex></expan> Sicinio <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ubli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>iberto</ex></expan> Germ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ano</supplied> <lb n="2"/>pis<supplied reason="lost">tori</supplied> <lb n="3"/>Caeciliae <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibertae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex cert="low"/></expan><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="4"/>Sicinia <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ubli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilia</ex></expan> Germ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ana</supplied> <lb n="5"/>matri et <supplied reason="lost">patri</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Elf aneinanderpassende Fragmente einer Marmortafel. Z. 1: statt Germ[ano?] auch Germ[aniano?] denkbar. Z. 3: vom C(?) ist die linke untere Ecke der Rundung erhalten. Z. 4: statt Germ[ana?] auch Germ[aniana?] denkbar.</p>
